=========================

1. WHAT IS AN API?

=========================

API = Application Programming Interface

It allows communication between software systems

Example: Weather API, Payment API, etc.

=========================

2. REST API BASICS

=========================

HTTP Methods:

GET    -> Retrieve data

POST   -> Send data

PUT    -> Update data

DELETE -> Delete data

=========================

3. WORKING WITH REQUESTS

=========================

import requests

Example GET request

url = "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts" response = requests.get(url)

print("Status Code:", response.status_code) print("First Post:", response.json()[0])

=========================

4. JSON HANDLING

=========================

data = response.json()

Access JSON

print("Title:", data[0]['title']) 

Convert Python -> JSON

import json json_data = json.dumps(data) print("JSON String Sample:", json_data[:100])

=========================

5. PUBLIC API PRACTICE

=========================

Example: Random User API

url = "https://randomuser.me/api/" res = requests.get(url) user = res.json()

print("Random User Name:", user['results'][0]['name']['first'])

=========================

6. BUILD YOUR OWN API (FLASK)

=========================

from flask import Flask, jsonify, request

app = Flask(name)

Sample data

students = [ {"id": 1, "name": "Sanjog"}, {"id": 2, "name": "Ram"} ]

@app.route('/') def home(): return "API is running"

@app.route('/students', methods=['GET']) def get_students(): return jsonify(students)

@app.route('/students', methods=['POST']) def add_student(): new_student = request.json students.append(new_student) return jsonify({"message": "Student added"})

=========================

7. API WITH DATA SCIENCE MODEL

=========================

Example: Simple ML Model API

from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression import numpy as np

Training data

X = np.array([[1], [2], [3], [4]]) y = np.array([2, 4, 6, 8])

model = LinearRegression() model.fit(X, y)

@app.route('/predict', methods=['POST']) def predict(): value = request.json['input'] prediction = model.predict([[value]]) return jsonify({"prediction": prediction.tolist()})

=========================

8. ERROR HANDLING & BEST PRACTICES

=========================

try: bad_response = requests.get("https://invalid-url.com") bad_response.raise_for_status() except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print("Error:", e)

Tips:

- Always check status_code

- Use try/except

- Validate input data

- Use environment variables for API keys.

=========================

RUN FLASK APP

=========================

if name == 'main': app.run(debug=True)